-- InterContinental Hotels Revenue Per Room Rises on Africa, Asia
-- B y   D a l i a   F a h m y
-- 2013-11-05T07:32:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-05/intercontinental-hotels-revenue-per-room-rises-on-africa-asia.html
InterContinental Hotels Group Plc (IHG) ,
the world’s largest provider of hotel accommodation, said third-quarter revenue per room increased, lifted by Asia,  Africa  and
the Middle East.  Revenue per available room, a measure of occupancy and
rates known as revpar, increased 3.3 percent from a year
earlier, Denham, England-based company said in a statement
today. The average daily room rate rose 1.7 percent.  “Despite the ongoing challenges in some of our markets,
current trading trends give us confidence for the rest of the
year,” Chief Executive Officer Richard Solomons said in the
statement.  Revpar at InterContinental’s hotels in Asia, the Middle
East and Africa advanced 5.4 in the third quarter, the company
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
